inn1.comm: gentle medium pace, around 126 kmph, in the channel outside off and Karthik shoulders arms
this one tilts in towards the middle and Karthik leans forward, bat and pad close together, to gently tap it to the on side of the pitch
back of length outside off stump line, pushed out to extra cover
around the off stump line, from a length, nudged to the on side
straightens outside off, Vijay presses back to tap it to point
curves away ever so gently from the off stump line, defended out to covers
drifts his first delivery down the leg side for a wide
another one that drifts in but this time on the leg stump line and hits the pad
quicker, moving into leg and middle line, flicked to backward square-leg fielder
goes down for the big sweep but doesn't connect properly .
moves back, waits for the ball to slid into the middle and leg line, and turns it to backward square-leg
slips just outside leg and Karthik quickly goes down on his knee to sweep it over short fine-leg fielder.
finally, switches his line to just outside off and Karthik gets forward to defend
on the middle stump line, Vijay goes back to tap it towards short midwicket
moves in towards the off stump line, full in length, Vijay defends to the off side.
fuller, on the middle, Vijay is late in getting forward and manages to push the ball towards mid-on.
straightens on the off stump line, length delivery but Vijay prefers to go back to defend
slips this one down the leg side for a wide. Vijay has a chat with the square-leg umpire I think ..and he moves back to his crease ..
straightens just outside off and Vijay waits on his back foot to push it to point
back of length, moves towards middle stump line and Vijay goes back to work it to the on side
on the leg and middle line, rolls away to the on side
just moves down the leg side.. perhaps brushed the pad .. Karthik had allowed to let it go
leans forward to defend to the off side
quicker but again moving down the leg side. Yet another wide. Dangerous line this  from Price.
on the off and middle this time, so much better, Karthik goes back to defend
but  back to original programming - another one that moves down leg side.
goes back to chip the delivery just short of very short midwicket
another one that comes in with the arm, nagging delivery, on the middle and leg, DK just manages to stab it to the on side
in the channel outside off, straightens, pushed out to point
goes  back and across to run down a short-of-length delivery to third man

fullish, on the leg and mdidle, line, tries to flick and might have got a thin edge and the ball rolls to the leg side .. Taibu dives full stretch, makes a half-stop. He gets up, flings his gloves off his hand, and rushes after the ball
on the off stump line, pushed out to short cover
length delivery on the middle stump line, Vijay, as ever, goes back to tap it towards mid-on
on the legs and Vijay flicks it slightly wide of backward square-leg fielder who gets a hand on it and takes some pace off the ball
leans forward to ease the ball towards long-on
stretches forward to squeeze the ball to the on side and Ray Price does his dramatic follow-through .. he picks the ball and takes a few steps towards Vijay.
goes back to punch this one to long-on
another one that sails down the leg side
fuller, on the middle and off line, driven to long-on
on the off and middle line, eased to short cover
goes back to punch the ball back to Price who flings it to Taibu
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
leans across to defend to point region
takes couple of steps down the track, Blignaut shortens the length and also gets it to shape it away from DK who has a poke at it and is beaten
short delivery outside off stump, run down to third man
length delivery around the off stump and Vijay pushes it to short cover
leans forward to defend to the off side
the nagging line and length on the off and middle, defended on the front foot
gets forward to push it to the off side
full on a length around off, pushed out to short cover
shorter in length and Vijay goes back to clip it wide of midwicket
arm ball on the middle stump line, from back of length, Karthik goes back to work it past square-leg
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
leans forward to drive to left of mid-off for a single
goes back, waits for the length delivery to arrive and steers it to point
gentle outswinger and Vijay lets it pass through
the surprise bouncer and Vijay ducks under
length delivery on the middle and off, pushed towards mid-on for a quick single
leans forward to ease the full delivery to long-on
on the middle stump line, turned to square-leg
plays a gentle reverse paddle, of the back fo the bat,  to pick a single
stays back to wrist it to square-leg
on the middle and leg line, turned to backward square-leg
leans forward to work the fuller delivery to midwicket for a single
flighted on the middle, on driven to long-on ..
turns in to the middle and leg line, worked to backward square-leg fielder
on the middle stump line, turned to square-leg
on the middle stump line, dabbed to left of backward square-leg fielder for a singel
turns in quickly on the leg stump line, Vijay tries to clip it away and is hit on the pad
goes back to punch it past the non striker
goes back to clip the off break to deep midwicket region
floated outside off stump, dabbed to the off side
Whoa! A shot of intent. A shot of purpose. Stop the press. Shout to your neighbours, they have played a shot. Short in length and outside off and DK geos back to cut it hard to the point boundary
leans forward to defend back down the pitch
a gentle long-hop that begged and cried for punishment and DK pulls it to the midwicket boundary
short again, pulled down to midwicket
flighted delivery, pushed down the ground, and Lamb's diving effort can't prevent a single
shorter, hit towards straight midwicket
strays too far down the leg side
flighted into the pads, worked away for one
topspinner, just outside off, doesn't turn in, Vijay plays it back to the bowler
around middle and off, no room, defended back
takes half a step down the pitch and pushes this to long-on for one
short ball, Vijay cuts, can't get it past cover-point
fuller, worked with the turn, finds square leg
charges at him, always intending to just push it down the ground for one, which he does
goes back in the crease and forces a shortish ball past midwicket
stays back to a fullish delivery, and pushes it into the on side
quick run, after helping it just to the right of midwicket
fired down the leg side, and the shortening of the length allows Karthik to go on a knee and paddle it past short fine
floater outside off, Karthik cuts, and nearly chops it onto the stumps. It not only evades the stumps, also gets them a single to short fine
forward-defensive from Vijay
comes down the track and pushes a shortish delivery past midwicket
stays on the back foot and punches on the up, but finds cover
turning into the pads, helped away to deep backward square
full delivery pushed to long-on for one
goes back to punch it to long-on
pushed to the off side this time
goes back and across to cut it through backward point
spins in to the middle stump line, tapped to the on side
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
Oh well .. DK is gone now .. He went for the reverse paddle and top edged a dolly of a catch to Taibu. It popped up gently and Taibu collected it. Thank you come again
goes right back to defend
floated full outside off, stretches forward to defend
leans across to on drive it from around off stump line to long-on
goes back to turn it past square-leg
gets on the back foot to tap it towards non-striker
flighted outside off, driven back to the bowler
on the off stump line, pushed back down the track
goes back to tap it to covers
leans forward to turn it to midwicket for a single
gets well back to wrist the off break to short midwicket
just outside off, punched off the back foot
leans forward to turn it to square-leg for a single
gets forward to defend to short midwicket
quicker, on the middle stump line, wristed past midwicket

And after all that plodding and meandering around .. he is gone now..  Suddenly, against the run of play, he rushed down the track and tried to play the big off drive. The ball was a drifter; it floated away from the bat and Taibu did the rest. A strangle little innings is over.
on the middle stump line, turns, worked to midwicket
goes back and across to defend to point
flighted on the leg stump line, flicked through midwicket
turns towards off and middle line, punched off the back foot and the short cover fielder moves to his right to make a tumbling stop
on the middle stump line, again punched of the back foot and again short cover intercepts
leans forward to defend to covers
moves forward to ease the flighted legbreak to long-off
turns with bounce, pushed out to cover point
gets on the back foot to punch it through extra cover
works the ball from around off stump to short midwicket
quicker, flatter and down the leg side, swept away for a single
Edged over the slip fielder. Virat went back to cut and the ball flew of the edge but went quickly over Masakadza at slip
quickish, on the middle and leg, nudged to the on side
gets back to work the off break to deep midwicket for a single
flighted legbreak, pushed to short cover.
the lone slip watches Virat push the ball to the off side of the pitch
lands it just outside leg, dabbed to short midwicket
flighted legbreak outside off and Virat stretches across to drive to short cover
straightens on the middle stump line, punched down to long-off
gets back to tap the ball to short midwicket.
gets on to the back foot and punches it to deep cover
on the back foot and works it to short midwicket
on the leg and middle line, pushes it past square-leg
leans forward to defend it back down the pitch
on the middle and leg, clipped past square-leg
turns slowly to the middle and leg line, Rohit tries to whip it to the on side and edges it to the off ...
presses back to turn it to midwicket
turns away from the off stump line, cut away wide of sweeper cover
leans forward to push the ball to mid-on
flighted on the middle and off, driven with the turn to long-off
turns from the middle and leg line, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up around the off stump line, driven to long-off
leans forward to square drive to point
moves forward and across to push the ball into spaces on the off side
goes back to punch it to the right of sweeper cover for couple of runs. It was slightly short in length and that allowed Virat to play that shot
short in length again , cut to sweeper cover
turns to the middle stump line, pushed down to long-on

Utseya takes out Virat. Nice work from Taibu. It was a flighted delivery that turned in  from outside off, Virat tried to work it to the on side, the ball hits the edge and bounds off Taibu's shoulder and he catches it on the rebound.
flighted leg break on the middle, driven to long-off
just outside off, Raina shapes to defend and the ball rolls away of the edge to third man
slightly short in length, cut to point

Slight drama on the middle and leg line, pushed towards mid-on and since it's his call, Rohit rushes on ... Raina was caught ball watching but manages to get across in time. The wild throw didn't help Zimbabwe' cause. Taibu had to really jump to grab it from well over his head.
works it to square-leg for a single
turns in from outside leg and hits the pad
slip in place and Raina goes back to punch this one to deep cover
turns in towards off, Rohit goes back to punch it to long-off
leans forward to defend to the off side

Raina is run out They had some problem in the last over as well. Raina is out this time ... He pushed it to right of short extra cover for a single. It was his call but Rohit thinks its too risky call to accept and stays put. Raina turns back and even dives but can't beat the direct hit from Blignaut. Raina has to go.
fullish, on the legs, rolls off the boot to short fine-leg region
gets forward to punch it to long-off
turns in from leg and middle line, punches to the on side
leans forward to turn it to midwicket
flighted around off stump, turned to the on side and Cremer makes a lunging stop
similar delivery and this time jadeja hits it straight back to the bowler

Rohit is run out Loverly drama there. Zimbabwe are calling all the shots here. It was pushed towards midwicket and Rohit isoff for the single but Jadeja sends him back. Rohit turns, Chigumbura swoops on the ball and throws it to the bowler who breaks the stumps
almost a catch It was the googly, Jadeja doesn't pick it and checks his shot . the ball is the air but flies over the bowler
slip in place. off break from round the stumps, cut to backward point
on the legs, swept to the on side .. doesn't connect well

loud shout for lbw .Close call ... it pitched on the leg and middle stump line and just about straightened .. Jadeja had a lame defensive poke at it, bat well behind the pad and was struck. It would have hit the leg stump.
leans forward to play the off drive for a single
leans forward to defend it back to Utseya
fuller, worked back to the bowler
shout for lbw but this one was  going down the leg side. Jadeja went back and tried to flick but missed.
leans forward to on drive to long-on
turns to the pads, clipped behind square-leg
tossed outside off, driven down to long-on
leans forward to defend on the front foot

comical drama Yusuf you beauty! He went for the lunging paddle sweep shot but slipped and fell.. almost does a full split! the ball bounced awkwardly and he manages to stab it to short fine-leg ... Yusuf hobbles across to the other end and holds his right toe.
gets forward to push it away
Brave man. Tries that paddle sweep again and this time connects
gets forward to ease it to the on side
on the middle and leg, worked wide of midwicket
stretches well forward and across to turn the off break from outside off to midwicket
skips down the track and drives to long-off.
goes back to work the leg break to square-leg
googly from middle and leg, Jadeja plays it of the pitch, taps it to the on side

shout for lbw ... good shout that. It landed just outside off, turned in, moved past the attempted flick and struck the pad in front of middle and leg. it would have hit the leg stump. Jadeja has escaped two close shouts so far .. hmmm
gets forward to defend to the off side
on the leg and middle line, squeezed past square-leg
The rare long hop from Cremer and Jadeja pulls it to midwicket boundary
pushes his first delivery of the new spell down the leg side and it brushes the pad en route to Taibu
short in length, on the off stump line, Yusuf taps it ever so gently back down the track
fuller but again down the leg side, rolls of the pad
slower one outside off, Yusuf tries to adjust and cuts but straight to cover
on the middle stump line, pushed back to Blignaut
aaha! the bouncer arrives and Yusuf tries to get away from it but the ball bounds off his left shoulder and rolls to point
stays back to defend to midwicket
turns in to jadeja who defends to square-leg
stretches forward to defend the leg break
short in length ,turns to the leg stump line, pulled to deep square-leg ,.. the ball was in the air the fielder at backward square-leg dived to his right but couldn't reach
turns this one along the ground for a single
flighted leg break on the leg and middle line, on driven to long-on
short in length just outside off, worked past square-leg for a single
full in length outside off, square driven to point
full in length outside off, punched through to deep point
back of length around off and middle, Yusuf stays back to push it to point
fullish just outside leg stump line, flicked down to fine-leg
back of length just outside off stump, punched to backward point
shout for lbw .. a flighted leg break on the middle stump line and Yusuf pushed forward to defend and I think got an inside edge on to his pad. That must have saved him.
leans forward to push to cover point
just outside off stump, tapped to backward point
slightly short of length, cut away to sweeper cover
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
Cremer offers his second long hop for the day. Yusuf puts it out its misery. he pulls it over midwicket boundary.
leans forward to turn to the on side
stays back to work it to midwicket
quicker, on the off stump line, pushed down to long-on

Dead plumb in front! Ray Price gets yet another international wicket with his arm ball. It landed just outside off and skidded in towards middle. Yusuf was pushing forward to defend but the bat was well outside the line of the delivery.
huge shout for lbw It was slower in pace, moved in towards middle stump line and hits the pad. Was there an inside edge? The bat was close to the ball  .. hope they show replays
goes back to stab it to the on side
outside the off stump and straightens , Jadeja is beaten, pushing inside the line
turns this to fine-leg

For a moment Mishra had transformed to Bravo. He sashayed down the track and played that stylish whippy lofted on drive that Bravo does so well. But of course its just Mishy. It doesn't cover much distance and the long-on fielder ran in to collect that.
leans well forward to defend
drops it short and Jadeja pulls it over the leaping square-leg fielder
turns in towards the middle and off line, punched to long-on
turns down the leg side ..
goes back to work it to midwicket
leans forward to deflect it to the on side
clips it to square-leg fielder
punches it off the back foot
tossed full on the middle, goes for the sweep and edges it to short fine-leg
rushes down the track and heaves the flighted off break over long-off. India are on 140
pushes this one to the off side
on the pads, rolls away to the on side
quicker, cut to point
goes back to clip it past square-leg
lands outside leg, turned to the on side
quicker, straightens outside leg, nudged to short fine-leg
goes back to nudge to the on side
Wallop! Jadeja clears the front foot and lofts the flighted off break high over long-on
on the legs, rolls of the pad for a leg bye
moves down the track and drives to long-on
fullish, on the middle, checks his shot .. and the ball rolls to the on side
drives the full delivery to long-on
on the middle and off line, pushed to the off side
on the middle stump line, swiped away past square-leg
Another ugly swipe across the line .. the ball goes of the edge to right of midwicket
goes for the big hit to the on side.. the ball rolls away of the pad
on the leg stump line, chipped in the air but short of the advancing deep midwicket
backs away and carves the full delivery towards straight boundary
stays back and heaves, doesn't connect properly, to left of mid-on
quickish off break and Dinda just about manages to get an inside edge on to his pad
goes for the big slog across the line but doesn't connect properly. Again.
heaves the full delivery towards long-on
short in length just outside off, cut past point
Dinda finally connects with one of those leg-side slogs. This one flies away to the backward square-leg boundary
moves outside leg and pushes the ball to cover
dropped by Cremer at long-on What a mess. It was hit straight to him and it went into his palms and popped right out.
low full toss and Jadeja smashes it to wide long-on boundary
just outside leg stump line, goes for the sweep, the ball rolls away to short third man
dropped by the bowler  Dinda went down the track and mishit it just over Lamb who jumps but can't hold on

Chance of a run out. The failed sweep shot saw the ball roll away to the off side .. Taibu was very quick to get off the blocks, picked the ball and dived forward to flick it to the bowler who doesn't collect cleanly .. Jadeja was out of his crease
And some one takes a catch. Finally. Taylor it is. It was the mis-hit slog and Taylor ran in from deep midwicket to collect it
quickish, shorter in length, turned to square-leg
from round the stumps, full in length, around off stump, pushed to short extra over
slower one but slips down the leg side
bouncer that moved from just outside leg to the off-stump line.. Ojha had a lame poke at it. Almost fatal.
on the middle stump line, defended to the off side
on the off stump line, steered to backward point
gets forward to play it away quietly
on the pads, turned past square-leg and he will retain the strike. Oh well...!
lands full just outside leg, goes past the attempted flick and hits the pad
short in length ,Ojha can't pierce that field on the off side
goes past the off stump, Ojha is beaten, trying to push it to third man
gets forward to drive it past the diving bowler
drives to covers .. no run
retains the strike with a drive to long-on
leans forward to drive to the off side
short in length, moves in from outside leg, turned to midwicket
in the zone outside off stump, Ojha tries to run it down to third man and is beaten
short in length, on the off stump line, pushed wide of short cover for a single
slower one that moves in from outside leg stump, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
on the middle stump line, squeezed out to backward point
goes down the track to drive down to long-on .. two fifties in successive games against Zimbabwe ..
goes for the hoick and is hit on the pad
gets a single with a drive to the on side
goes for the big heave .. mistimes it to midwicket and they run hard to come back for the second run
low full toss, sliced away to long-off
gets down the track and mistimes it to long-off. Ojha, again, retains the strike. Cho cute!
short in length around off stump line, shovels it over point
banged in short and Jadeja flat-bats it straight to long-off. He hung around in middle, got a fifty and pushed India towards 200
short and outside off, carved to deep backward point region
short in length, cuts in to the middle, pushed out to the bowler
full delivery, whipped to left of long-on
slower one, hit to midwicket for a single .. and the fielder missed the stumps at the non-striker's end .. had it hit the stumps, they could have got a run out

inn2.comm: in the zone outside off stump, left alone
in the channel outside off stump, left alone for Karthik
short in length, just outside off, tapped close on the off side for a quick single
short in length and outside off stump, Taylor allows it to pass go
back of length, tilts in towards middle and off line, pushed out to the on side
well outside the off stump, close to that wide line, left alone
just outside off stump line, pushed out to point
the arm ball on the off stump line, punched to short cover
on the middle and leg line, squeezed to square-leg
lands on a length around off and turns away, Taylor was lured into the off drive and was beaten
flighted on the off and middle line, driven to long-off where Jadeja makes a fine mess of it ..Extra run
pushes this one to coveres
wide outside off stump .. he was close to bowling a wide in the last delivery of the previous over as well
short in length, on the hips, tucked behind square for a single
One slip in place. It lands back of length and in the region outside off stump, Masakadza shoulders arms
short delivery, pulled to left of midwicket where Jadeja makes up for his earlier lapse with a diving stop and also has a shy at the non-striker's end
length delivery homing in on the off stump, pushed out to covers
length delivery tilting in to the middle and off line, pushed out to mid-on
back of length around middle stump line, eased towards mid-on
on the middle and off line, defended to the off side
full on the leg stump line, turned straight to midwicket
leans forward to defend it back down the pitch
quicker one, skidding on the middle and off line, squeezed out to the on side
slower, on the off, pushed out to Raina at short extra cover
leans forward to ping long-off
The first shot of intent. Taylor got into a nice position to play the punchy forcing shot of the back foot through covers.
And again but this time Raina intercepts at short cover.
slower one, fullish, just outside off, driven to the off side
back of length on the middle, Taylor goes back and across to tap it towards square-leg
fullish, on the pads, Masa fails to connect with the flick shot and is hit on the pad
slower one outside off, Masakadza checks his shot and the ball rolls to the keeper
leans forward to defend to the on side
unfurls the paddle sweep this time and picks up a couple of runs
gets down the track and tries to play a Shastri-like defensive shot .. the ball rolls of the pad
moves forward to chip it over wide mid-on region .. neatly done ...
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
rushes down the track, reaches the pitch of the flighted delivery and wallops it along the ground past mid-on
hurls a short delivery and Taylor swivels of the front foot to play a crunchy pull shot. He had enough time in the world to pull it twice if he wanted ..
in the zone outside off, left alone
fullish, on the middle and leg, driven to left of mid-on where Ojha lungses but fails to stop it cleanly ..
short in length, just outside off, defends and it back spins and rolls past the off stump

Fab cover drive. It was a full delivery just outside off and he creamed it through a packed off-side field. Vijay gave chase and tried to push it back with a dive but he touched the boundary line .. oh well.,the third umpire doesn't think so ..
short in length, punched to short extra cover
fullish delivery on the middle stump line, flicked to the on side
on the middle and leg, clipped past square-leg for couple of runs
length delivery just outside off, defended on the front foot
short in length, pushed to mid-on
leans forward to defend to short midwicket
Imperiously classy! It was slightly short and he pulled it of the front foot. The white ball sailed over midwicket boundary. Whack!
leans forward to push it to mid-on
takes a couple of steps down the track and mishits it to mid-on
length delivery outside off ,slashed away to third man
a slower one that was telegraphed even before he thought of it ! and it's a wide outside off stump
length delivery on the off stump line, nudged to square-leg and they run superbly to get two!
Fabuliciously stylish! It was a full delivery outside off and Taylor played a delightful off drive  to the left of mid-off..
gets behind the line of this short-of-length delivery and pushes it to the off side
Slip in. Hamilton stretches forward to defend
Shot! Hamilton sashays down the track and crashes the flighted delivery over mid-on. So easily done.
Crack of whip! It was a short delivery and Masakadza cuts it to through covers.
leans well forward to defend
flighted full on the off stump line, driven to long-off
slider coming in from just outside off, Taylor leans forward to defend and is hit on the pad outside off
floated full outside leg stump and Masakadza sweeps it to fine-leg and Mishra runs back from short fine-leg position to make a diving stop
leans forward to off drive to wide long-off
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
on the middle and leg line, on driven to long-on
turns away from the off stump, squeezed to point
on the leg and middle line, turned to short fine-leg
on the middle and off line, squeezed out to mid-on
leans forward to on drive to long-on
Taylor's second successful chip shot over mid-on. He takes a couple of steps down the track and chips it over wide mid-on
reaches forward to whip it through midwicket
stretches well forward to defend
His third wonderful chip shot and this time he gets a boundary. He skipped down the track and plays a whippy lofted drive to long-on boundary
goes back to turn it to short fine-leg
leans well forward to defend back down the track
moves down the track and pushes it to covers
on the off stump line and defended on the front foot
moves down the track and and on driven to long-on
leans forward to off drive to long-off
leans well forward to drive to the off side
on the middle and leg line, turned behind square-leg
Nice! he went on to his back foot and plays a punchy shot through covers .. the ball stops just before the line... they could have run a four there but Taylor was jogging
leg break outside off, squeezed to point
gets forward to on drive to long-on
moves down the track and defends
on the leg stump line, turned to midwicket
straightens on the middle stump line, pushed out to the on side
slower, more flight, defended to the off side
on the middle, eased down to long-off
leans forward to push it down to the bowler
leans well forward to drive the leg break to long-off
slows up the pace, driven to long-off
leans forward to drive to the covers
pushes it to the off side for a single
stays back to punch it to the bowler
eases it back to Amit who throws it back to the keeper
leans forward to defend to the off side
moves forward to drive to long-off. That;'s his fifty. Superb innings so far. a really yummy cover drive and couple of stylish chip shots
stays back to punch it to long-off
on the middle stump line, wristed to midwicket
slows up the pace, on the off stump line, driven to long-off
goes down the track and pushes it towards mid-on
just outside off stump, pushed out to covers
flighted outside off, on driven to long-on
stays back to punch to the bowler
just on the off and middle line, pushed out to point
slider on the middle, punched down to long-on
on the legs, flicked past square-leg
on the legs, turned to backward square-leg
Thwack! Taylor went down on his knee to play the sweep shot.
on the middle stump line, driven to long-off
on a length, on driven to long-on
on the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
reaches forward to off drive
length delivery outside off, pushed out to point
full in length and just down the leg side, glanced away to fine-leg
length delivery on the middle, punched down to long-on
short in length on the middle, turned to midwicket
short delivery on the off, steered to point
on a length around off stump, pushed out to cover point
goes back to clip it through midwicket
on the off stump line, cut to point
lands outside leg , turns, Taylor goes for the sweep and is hit on the body
leans forward to defend back down the pitch
on the off and middle line, Taylor had pressed his front leg dangerously across but managed to get the bat in front
gets forward to punch it to long-on
back of length , tilts in towards off stump, punched to long-on
banged in short, mistimes the pull to square-leg
short in length on the off stump line, punched down to long-on
full delivery, outside off stump, Hamilton tries to jab it away and the ball goes through to the keeper
slower one, on a length on the middle, turned to midwicket

Dinda's fascination with his slower ones continue. They can be picked so early and easily and this one has been pulled away to the boundary. Zimbabwe have been clinical, professional and have crushed India here.
